Page 6: Introduction to TCP & UDP
TCP & UDP
Whenever a computer wants to communicate with another computer, the communication between those two computers needs to be good and reliable.
The goal is to guarantee that data is received correctly.
Examples:
If we want to view a webpage, we try to view the file completely.
Similarly, if we want to download a file, we will download the file complete rather than just a part of a file.
TCP (Transmission Control Protocol)
It is the main protocol used in TCP/IP Networks.
TCP is used to guarantee that all data is received in order.
Without TCP, some of the data could be missing or out of order.
Characteristics of TCP:
Connection-oriented.
Reliable.
Ordered delivery.
Error checking.
Slower.
Used In:
HTTP / HTTPS.
File downloads.
Banking apps.

