Page 7: TCP Order & Three-Way Handshake
Data Structure & Order:
TCP handles data in a structured way with a proper sequence (Header → Body → Footer).
Without proper order, data transmission would be mixed and messed up (e.g., a webpage's footer appearing where the header should be).
File Download Example: A file might be saved in a corrupted way and won't work clearly if the parts are not ordered correctly.
Connection Establishment:
TCP is a connection-oriented session where it must connect clearly.
It uses a "HAND SHAKE 3-way" for connecting.
Before sending any data, it will first establish the connection.
The Three-Way Handshake Process:
SYN: Client says "CAN I CONNECT?".
SYN-ACK: Server says "Yes I acknowledge".
ACK: Client confirms.

